I use Godot outside steam (because I don't use steam so often anymore), and I'm writing this review only to spread the word, and let know people how good it is. 
I use Godot mostly for free-time projects and experiments.

I used Unity in the past, and even if I liked it, due to the massive amount of tutorials and information, was hard to find the "right way" to do things. 
I mean, you can implement things in many ways, but in Unity's community there was always some guy that was telling to do "this" because was cleaner and easier to maintain, another guy told you to do "that" because was simpler to implement. Unity is powerful, but organizing a (relatively complex) project it's not a simple task, at least it wasn't for me.
In Godot I haven't this problem anymore, because the "easy" way, it's the "right" way. The Node-Scene-Tree organization it's a really easy concept to grasp. I can write all my ideas on paper and already have a clear vision in my mind on how those concept will be transferred in Godot.

After sharing my experience, some pros and cons:
Pros:
+easy to learn;
+easy to organize a project;
+source code avaliable;
+ability to write in C++ for high performance tasks;
+small executable (less than 50 MB in windows 64bit);
+fast opening and loading of the editor, and also fast loading of projects;
+great community, that is growing really fast, that is contributing with tutorials and examples;
+developers and contributors are doing a great job, now Godot is almost equal, feature wise, to much more famous engines.

Cons:
-regarding technology and number of features, not already on par with engines like Unity or Unreal, but it won't last long ;-)

Download it now!
